TY  - JOUR
AU  - Thompson, James R.
T1  - Counterparty Risk in Financial Contracts: Should the Insured Worry About the Insurer?*
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/08/01
DO  - 10.1162/qjec.2010.125.3.1195
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 125
IS  - 3
SP  - 1195
EP  - 1252
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We analyze the effect of counterparty risk on financial insurance contracts, using the case of credit risk transfer in banking. This paper posits a new moral hazard problem on the insurer side of the market, which causes the insured party to be exposed to excessive counterparty risk. We find that this counterparty risk can create an incentive for the insured party to reveal superior information about the likelihood of a claim. In particular, a unique separating equilibrium may exist, even in the absence of any costly signaling device.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/qjec.2010.125.3.1195
ER  - 



